  "prompt": "What universities does CRA International recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "CRA International, also known as Charles River Associates, typically recruits new graduates from a range of universities, often focusing on institutions known for strong programs in economics, business, finance, and related fields. While specific universities can vary by region and year, they often look for candidates from reputable universities with robust analytical programs.\n\nIn terms of majors, CRA International commonly seeks graduates from fields such as:\n\n- Economics\n- Business Administration\n- Finance\n- Mathematics or Applied Mathematics\n- Statistics\n- Data Science\n- Political Science\n- Public Policy\n- Engineering (particularly for specific consulting roles)\n\nThe company values strong analytical and quantitative skills, so candidates with a strong foundation in these areas are generally preferred. Additionally, having experience with research, data analysis, and problem-solving can be advantageous in the recruitment process.",
